To get git bash to run in powershell do this 
& 'C:\Program Files\Git\bin\sh.exe' --login

git add. 
git commit -m "message here" 

For python venv stuff 

virtualenv <venv name> #ignore the <>'s 

To activate the venv
.\BirthdayBot\Scripts\activate

to create the python requirements.txt file do this when the venv is activated 
pip freeze > requirements.txt

